-- Lexer error: a `\u{…}` char escape is still ONE codepoint and must be closed by
-- `'` immediately (#668). `'\u{41}z` is unterminated — `readCharUnicode` used to
-- resume scanning past a closing quote it never checked for, so this lexed as
-- `TChar "A"` at exit 0 (the #668 Symptom-A silent accept, via the `\u{…}` path).
x = '\u{41}z
